    public interface NativeResource
extends java.lang.AutoCloseable
    Classes that implement this interface are associated with one or more native resources. These resources must be explicitly freed when a class instance is no longer used, by calling the free() method.

    This interface extends AutoCloseable, which means that implementations may be used as resources in try-with-resources statements.
